I understand that some people have mixed feelings over the profit guidance announced this evening  but I like to bring everyone's attention to this sentence in ICG's press release "Notwithstanding the above  theGroup is still expected to record profits for 2H2020 and FY2020. The overall financial position of the Group remains healthy."So hey  it isn't too bad after all! While ICG's earnings have been affected by the loss in forex exchanges  it's still going to record a Full Year profit. And we all know 2020 has been a challenging.Anyways  here's what I expect of the FY2020 earnings At least $10m profits  why?1H2020: 6.001m profit (23% increase from 2019)2H2020: at least 5.000m profit (half of the 2H earnings recorded in 2019).Moving on  it's also quite clear that ICG is slated to be in a good position with COVID situation improving and oil prices recovering steadily (reducing forex losses). I believe the BBs are ready. 😄
